                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>n n(omine) D(omi)ni. C(on)stat me <persName key="#Priests #Monks"><name
                                ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">p(res)b(ite)r</rs> et <rs key="#Monks">monachus</rs>
                        atq(ue) p(re)positus, decanos <persName><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Ioh(anne)s</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">p(res)b(ite)r</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">mon(asterii)</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1487">S(an)c(t)i
                            Ap[o]llinaris [qui vocatur Novo]</orgName> una cum cunctos <rs
                            key="#Monks">fr(atre)s</rs> accepisse et accepi a vob(is)
                                <persName><name ref="Apollinaris">Apollinaris</name></persName>
                        filio quo(n)d(am) <persName><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Ioh(anni)s</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">pensione</rs> p(ro) [<rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >tres uncias</rs>] in integro q(ui) est posita in <rs key="#Fundi"
                            >fundum</rs> qui vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money" ref="#estates/2421"
                                ><placeName key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money"
                                >Colopedio</placeName></geogName> cu(m) om(n)ib(us) sibi
                        p(er)tinentib(us), <rs key="#Fines">territ[o]rio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#estates/2422"><placeName
                                key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#places/3515"
                            >Liv[iense]</placeName></geogName>, <rs key="#Plebs">plebe</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/1488">S(an)c(t)e
                            Reparate</orgName>, quas p(er) <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"
                            >enfiteusin</rs> tenere visi estis ad iure monasterii n(ost)ri, et p(er)
                        una[quamque in]dic(ione) <rs key="#Rent_in_money">din(arii) V</rs> tantu(m).
                        Unde p(ro) munim[i]ne v(est)ro feci vob(is) hoc deaccepto i(n) m(en)se
                        m[arcio], indic(ione) udecima, <placeName ref="#places/594"
                            >Rav(enne)</placeName>. Petrus monachus adque p(re)positus monasterii
                        S(an)c(t)i Apollenaris q(ui) v(ocatur) Novo in oc deaccepto s(ub)s(cripsi).
                        Ioh(anne)s p(res)b(ite)r et monachus adq(ue) d[ec]anos S(an)c(t)i Apolinaris
                        q(ui) vocat(ur) Novo in oc deaccepto s(ub)s(cripsi).</ab>
